    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section id="faq">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-header">
                <h2>‚ùì Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <p>Common questions about auto insurance in North Carolina</p>
            </div>
            
            <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                        <span>How can I lower my auto insurance rates?</span>
                        <svg class="faq-icon" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
                        </svg>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>There are several ways to reduce your auto insurance premiums:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Shop around:</strong> Compare quotes from multiple insurers annually</li>
                            <li><strong>Increase deductibles:</strong> Higher deductibles = lower premiums</li>
                            <li><strong>Bundle policies:</strong> Combine auto with home/renters insurance</li>
                            <li><strong>Maintain good credit:</strong> Better credit often means lower rates</li>
                            <li><strong>Drive safely:</strong> Avoid tickets and accidents</li>
                            <li><strong>Ask about discounts:</strong> Many go unclaimed</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                        <span>What factors affect my insurance rates in NC?</span>
                        <svg class="faq-icon" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
                        </svg>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>North Carolina insurers consider many factors when setting rates:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Driving record:</strong> Accidents and violations increase rates</li>
                            <li><strong>Age and experience:</strong> Younger drivers pay more</li>
                            <li><strong>Location:</strong> Urban areas typically cost more</li>
                            <li><strong>Vehicle type:</strong> Sports cars and luxury vehicles cost more</li>
                            <li><strong>Credit score:</strong> Better credit usually means lower rates</li>
                            <li><strong>Annual mileage:</strong> More driving = higher risk</li>
                            <li><strong>Coverage levels:</strong> More coverage costs more</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                        <span>Do I need uninsured motorist coverage if I have health insurance?</span>
                        <svg class="faq-icon" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
                        </svg>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Yes, you should keep uninsured motorist coverage even with health insurance:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Covers lost wages your health insurance won't pay</li>
                            <li>No health insurance deductibles or copays</li>
                            <li>Covers passengers who might not have health insurance</li>
                            <li>Provides coverage for pain and suffering</li>
                            <li>Required by NC law unless rejected in writing</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                        <span>How do NC insurance points affect my rates?</span>
                        <svg class="faq-icon" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
                        </svg>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>NC insurance points can significantly increase your rates:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>1 point:</strong> 30% rate increase</li>
                            <li><strong>2 points:</strong> 45% rate increase</li>
                            <li><strong>3 points:</strong> 60% rate increase</li>
                            <li><strong>4 points:</strong> 80% rate increase</li>
                            <li><strong>12 points (DUI):</strong> 340% rate increase</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>Note:</strong> Insurance points are different from DMV license points!</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

